<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>spy on someone • spy someone</xh5><p> <i>spy on someone—</i>watch or follow smb. secretly, usually with hostile intent: She was constantly <u>spied on</u>, written about, talked about, followed around.</p><p> <i>spy someone—</i>catch sight of smb.; notice a person: There is great danger if the hippopotamus <u>spies</u> the huntsman before he can throw his spear.</p> </entry>
